## AI-Facing Endpoints

{{- if .WithInteraction }}
- `POST /mcp` — MCP JSON-RPC endpoint (protocol version 2025-06-18)
  - `initialize` — capability negotiation and server info
  - `ping` — liveness check
  - `tools/list` / `tools/call` — discover and invoke service methods
  - `resources/list` / `resources/read` — read server-exposed data artifacts
  - `resources/templates/list` — discover parameterised resource URI patterns
  - `prompts/list` / `prompts/get` — list and render reusable prompt templates
  - `logging/setLevel` — adjust server log verbosity
  - `notifications/initialized` — complete the MCP handshake (notification, no response)
  - Supports Streamable HTTP transport: GET for SSE streams, DELETE for session termination
  - Supports MCP Sampling: server can request LLM completions from connected clients
{{- end }}
{{- if .WithSkill }}
- `GET /skill` — OpenAI-style tool discovery
- `GET /skill?format=mcp` — MCP-style tool discovery (schema only)
{{- end }}
- `GET /debug/routes` — runtime route inspection
- `GET /health` — health check

## Common Modifications

1. **Add business logic** → edit `service/<name>/service.go`
2. **Add endpoint middleware** → edit `endpoint/<name>/custom_chain.go`
3. **Add a new service or model** → run `microgen extend -check -out .` first, then use `-append-service` or `-append-model`
4. **Change AI tool behavior** → the tools are auto-registered from endpoints; change the underlying service logic instead

